en_602824_0	Troops in Kilinochchi area with the intention of promoting goodwill among civilians contributed to the commemoration of Deepavali on Tuesday (6) launching several projects.
en_602824_1	On the directions of Major General Vijitha Ravipriya, General Officer Commanding (GOC), 57 Division, 9 Vijayabahu Infantry Regiment (VIR) troops under command to the 571 Brigade conducted Shramadana campaigns and tree planting drives in the Malayalapuram, Paththini Amman Kovil premises and surrounding areas on the Deepavali day.
en_602824_2	Meanwhile, 6 Sri Lanka Sinha Regiment (SLSR) troops and 14 Sri Lanka National Guard (SLNG) troops under command to the 572 Brigade participated in separate offerings at Thottadi Amman Kovil and Kannei Amman Kovil respectively.
en_602824_3	Similarly, 15 Sri Lanka Sinha Regiment (SLSR) troops under command to the 573 Brigade attended a special Pooja in the Siththi Vinayagar Kovil.
en_602824_4	Meanwhile, 1 SLSR troops carried out a Shramadana in the Korankandu Hindu Kovil premises on account of the auspicious day, followed by a special Pooja.
en_602824_5	In the meantime, 3 Gajaba Regiment (GR) of the 574 Brigade took part in another Pooja at Mankulam Ganapathi Kovil.
en_602824_6	20 civilians joined troops for this self-help project.
